// @test regression/INV012-parser-sync-skips-nested
// @description A parse error deep inside a nested expression must not cascade into the top-level statements that follow. The parser's synchronize() routine should skip past the broken nested context to the next true top-level statement. See investigations/INV012-parser-sync-column-1/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
//@version=6
indicator("t")

// Function with a switch arm body that uses `:=` (reassignment).
// Our parser currently doesn't accept `:=` in this nested-switch-arm
// position — that's a real limitation, but it should produce ONE
// error, not a cascade across the rest of the script.
f() =>
    var int x = 0
    float result = switch close
        1.0 => 1
        =>
            x := 2
            x
    result

// These top-level calls must still parse and validate cleanly even
// though `f()` body has a parse error. plot must NOT be reported as
// "cannot be called from a local scope" — synchronize must have
// returned the parser to true top-level by here.
y = f()
plot(y)
plot(close)
